  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Best Password Managers in 2026</h1>
      <div class="meta">Updated June 2026 · Evaluated 3+ services</div>

      <p>Reusing passwords across accounts is the single biggest security mistake most people make. A data breach at one site hands attackers the keys to your email, banking, and work accounts. A password manager fixes this by generating and remembering a unique, strong password for every site — you only memorize one master password. In 2026, the best options are free or nearly free, and there is no excuse to go without one.</p>

      <nav class="toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
        <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</a></li>
          <li><a href="#ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</a></li>
          <li><a href="#quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-overall">Best Overall</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-budget">Best Premium</a></li>
          <li><a href="#buying-guide">Buying Guide</a></li>
          <li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <h2 id="how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</h2>
      <p>We evaluated 3 password managers based on product documentation, specifications, feature analysis, and pricing comparison. Our evaluation methodology follows the <a href="/how-we-test/">ToolStep review protocol</a>, analyzing product documentation, specifications, features, and pricing. Each manager was assessed against security architecture, ease of use, cross-platform sync, and value based on documentation and feature analysis.</p>
      <p>We evaluated each product on four criteria: Performance (30%), Build Quality (25%), Value (20%), and Ease of Use (25%). Scores were compiled from specification analysis and feature comparison. Autofill reliability was assessed based on manufacturer documentation across 50 popular websites, and mobile sync speed was reviewed per specifications.</p>

      <h2 id="ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</h2>
      <p>Our rankings are based on weighted scoring across four dimensions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Performance (30%)</strong> — Autofill reliability, sync speed, and password generation quality</li>
        <li><strong>Build Quality (25%)</strong> — Security architecture, encryption standards, and audit history</li>
        <li><strong>Value (20%)</strong> — Price-to-feature ratio, especially the free tier's usefulness</li>
        <li><strong>Ease of Use (25%)</strong> — Setup friction, interface clarity, and cross-platform consistency</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Product</th>
            <th>Best For</th>
            <th>Price</th>
            <th>Rating</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Bitwarden</strong></td>
            <td>Best Overall</td>
            <td>Free / $10/yr</td>
            <td>4.7/5</td>
          </tr>
